quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  22,56,Us roz baadshahi Allah ki hogi aur woh unke darmiyan faisla kardega. Jo iman rakhne waley aur amal e saleh karne waley hongey woh niyamat bhari jannaton mein jayenge
  22,57,Aur jinhon ne kufr kiya hoga aur hamari aayat ko jhutlaya hoga unke liye ruswakun azaab hoga
  22,58,"Aur jin logon ne Allah ki raah mein hijrat ki, phir qatal kardiye gaye ya marr gaye, Allah unko accha rizq dega aur yaqeenan Allah hi behtareen raaziq hai"
  22,59,Woh unhein aisi jagah pahunchayega jissey woh khush ho jayenge. Beshak Allah aleem (all knowing) aur haleem (Most Forbearing) hai
  22,60,"Yeh to hai unka haal, aur jo koi badla le, waisa hi jaisa uske saath kiya gaya, aur phir uspar zyadati bhi ki gayi ho, to Allah uski madad zaroor karega. Allah maaf karne wala aur darguzar karne wala hai"
  22,61,Yeh is liye ke raat se din aur din se raat nikalne wala Allah hi hai aur woh sami (sunney waala/ hears everything) o baseer (dekhne wala /sees everything) hai
  22,62,Yeh isliye ke Allah hi haqq hai aur woh sab baatil hain jinhein Allah ko chodh kar yeh log pukarte hain. Aur Allah hi baaladast (Supreme) aur buzurg (Exalted One) hai
  22,63,Kya tum dekhte nahin ho ke Allah aasman se pani barsata hai aur uski badaulat zameen sar-sabz ho jaati hai? Haqeeqat yeh hai ke woh lateef o khabeer hai (fully aware of everything)
  22,64,Usi ka hai jo kuch aasmano mein hai aur jo kuch zameen mein hai. Beshak wahi gani (All-Sufficient/ free of all wants) o hameed (praiseworthy) hai